# Docker and CI

## Docker

- **Base image:** `ruby:3.3.11-slim` with multi-stage build
- **Node:** Installed via nodenv (Node 24.x) for asset compilation
- **Yarn:** Use `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` â€” never modify `yarn.lock` in Docker builds
- **Assets:** Precompiled with `SECRET_KEY_BASE_DUMMY=1`
- **Runtime:** Non-root `rails` user; entrypoint at `bin/docker-entrypoint`

## docker-compose (split stacks)

Use `-f docker-compose.<stack>.yml`; each stack sets a top-level `name:` so volumes and networks do not collide across stacks.

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docker-compose.dev.yml` | Local dev: Postgres + Redis + `web` + `sidekiq` (bind-mounted app). Postgres container `membermanager-dev-postgres`, host DB port `5432`. |
| `docker-compose.test.yml` | Tests: thin Ruby image, bind-mounted app, cached Bundler volume; Postgres + Redis + `test` service. |
| `docker-compose.test.build.yml` | Same as test stack but forces a rebuild of the thin test image. |
| `docker-compose.lint.yml` | RuboCop (quick): prebuilt `member_manager_rubocop:latest`, bind-mounted app; no Postgres service. |
| `docker-compose.lint.build.yml` | Same as lint stack but **includes** a `build:` for `Dockerfile.rubocop`. |
| `docker-compose.server.yml` | Prod/staging-style: **no** Postgres service; set `DATABASE_URL` (or DB\_\* ) for external DB. Includes Redis for Sidekiq unless `REDIS_URL` points elsewhere. |

- **Dev migrate:** `docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml --profile tools run --rm migrate`
- **Tests:** `docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml run --rm test` â€” installs changed gems into the cached bundle volume and recreates the test DB before each run
- **Tests (image rebuild):** `docker compose -f docker-compose.test.build.yml run --rm test`
- **Lint (quick):** `docker compose -f docker-compose.lint.yml run --rm rubocop` â€” refresh image with `docker compose -f docker-compose.lint.build.yml build rubocop` when needed
- **Lint (full build):** `docker compose -f docker-compose.lint.build.yml run --rm rubocop`
- **Server migrate:** `docker compose -f docker-compose.server.yml --profile tools run --rm migrate`

Dev/test bind-mount the repo at `/rails`; test images should not copy application code. Lint bind-mounts at `/workspace`; server uses the built image only.

## GitHub Actions

- **ci.yml:** Runs on push/PR to `main`; sets up PostgreSQL 16 and Redis 7 as service containers; runs `bin/rails test`
- **release.yml:** Triggered by `v*` tags; runs tests then builds and pushes Docker image to `ghcr.io`
- Uses `ruby/setup-ruby` with bundler-cache and `actions/setup-node` with yarn cache
- Concurrency: cancels in-progress runs for the same ref
